5 INTRODUCTION

* Issue: 6-Revision: 2 - 15 OCT 24
The Operations Manual has been prepared in the English language;
The Operations Manual has been prepared in accordance to the conditions and limitations
contained in the AOC and with regards to the provisions of ECARs;
The Operations Manual contains the applicable policies, procedures, checklists and other
guidance or information necessary to comply with the applicable regulations, laws, rules and
EGYPTAIR’s standards;
The Operations Manual is produced and distributed in either hard copies or electronic
version. The content and appearance of both are identical;
Each hard copy of the Operations Manual is controlled and identified with a unique copy
number;
Operations Manual e.g. Training Manual, Maintenance Manual, Dispatch Manual...etc are
centrally controlled and coordinated through the Safety, Quality and Standardization
Department to ensure its compliance with EGYPTAIR’s standards in terms of document
control, information legibility and consistency, presentation compliance and regulations/
policies compliance;
To exercise control over the distribution of OM Part A, the hard copies are numbered.

The
Standardization Department maintains an up-to-date list of the manual holders together with
their copy number, name and title as appropriate;
Electronic version of the Operations Manual is distributed via intranet.egyptair.com/airlines-
portal.egyptair.com or Company iPad;
Electronic versions of the OM Part A contain bookmarks to ensure ease of content location;
Printed or copied samples are uncontrolled documents, thus they shall be considered
obsolete and shall not be used for operational purposes;
All operations personnel have either easy access to the Operations Manual electronic versions
or have been issued a hard copy of the Operations Manual, or parts thereof, that are relevant
to their duties;
Whenever operations personnel are unable to understand the English language, parts of the
Operations Manual relevant to their duties shall be translated into a language that they are
able to understand;
Throughout this manual, EgyptAir Airlines will be referred to as "EGYPTAIR" for simplicity and
clarity;
Flight Deck Crew Members in possession of a company IPad shall ensure that the latest
updates are downloaded;
OM Part A, OM Part D, OM Part F and OM Part L contain EGYPTAIR’s operational policies and
procedural matters. Should a conflict concerning operational policies or procedural matters
arise, OM Part A shall take precedence;
Operations personnel shall comply with the manufacturer’s operating limitations contained in
OM Part B;
Any differences from manufactures provided procedures, checklist and operations manual are
based on operational considerations and shall only be more restrictive;
In case of any difference arises from the OM Part B and procedures and checklists contained
in the operation manual, that are less restrictive, the chief pilot shall inform the
standardization manager by formal means of communications;
ADMINISTRATION AND CONTROL

It accounts for differences
between types, variants or individual aeroplanes. Material produced by EGYPTAIR for this part are supplemented or substituted by
applicable parts. AOM comprises of:
Aeroplane Flight Manual (AFM);
Flight Crew Operating Manual (FCOM);
Quick Reference Handbook (QRH);
Flight Crew Training/Techniques Manual (FCTM);
Weight and Balance Manual (WBM);
Minimum Equipment List (MEL);
Dispatch Deviation Guide (DDG);
Configuration Deviation List (CDL). It contains relevant checklists, and a description and instructions for the use of
emergency equipment and instructions relating to the actions to be taken in
emergencies. OM Part C (RM) Is the Jeppesen "Route and Airport Instructions and Information Manual". It
comprises of all instructions and information needed for the area of operation. OM Part D (TM) Is the "Training Manual", which outlines policies pertaining to all training and
checking activities, including the training programs and procedures to implement
those polices. Other Operations Manual which influence Flight Operations are:

ADMINISTRATION AND CONTROL

