SPM Station Procedure Manual. The Operations Manual and checklists have been developed to provide instructions, rules and
operational procedures for all kind of operations personnel. The human factors principles, which
have been observed in the design of the Operations Manual, checklists, forms and associated
procedures, ensure:

That all documents are prepared in a usable format for information presentation, at the
appropriate reading level and with the required degree of technical sophistication and clarity;
The use of effective and consistent labels, symbols, colors, terms, abbreviations, formats and
data fields; and;
That operational procedures are designed for simplicity, consistency and ease of use and to
minimize the need for special skills or abilities. NOTE In order to ensure that they are useable, identifiable and consistent with the
manufacturer specifications, aircraft manufacturer documentation e.g. SOPs,
Checklists... etc. are designed according to each particular manufacturer standards. The following key terms are used throughout the OM Part A to indicate the below meanings:

Term Meaning
shall, must
Positive imperative. To impose an obligation or a requirement, this manual uses
shall. Here, shall means the same as must. should Means that the application of a procedure or provision is recommended. may This term expresses a positive permission. shall not, must not These terms express an obligation, a negative command. Here, shall not means the
same as must not. need not This term expresses a negative permission.

1 Authority for Issuing Amendments

* Issue: 6-Revision: 2 - 15 OCT 24
Amendments to the Operations Manual may be issued as and when required;
Amendments to the Operations Manual are normally promulgated by means of revisions;
Amendments related to the Operations Manual shall, before being published and/or sent to
the ECAA for acceptance/approval, be sent to the Standardization Department for reviewing
and to the G.M. safety, Quality and Standardization who shall authorize those amendments;
EGYPTAIR' Operations Manual Part A and/or their amendments are either produced by a third
party i.e. aircraft manufacturer, JEPPESEN and TRS, or by the relevant section of Flight
Operations, or any suggestion from the operating crew after evaluation from the concerned
department;
Each concerned department is responsible for the following:
Making sure that the content of its related Operations Manual conforms to the latest
available and relevant regulations;
Making sure that amendments/revisions requiring deviation from the procedures and/or
checklists provided by the original aircraft manufacturer(s) are based on operational
considerations;
Following up on, and receiving, the ECAA acceptance/approval;
The retention of a master copy;
Version control (electronic documents);
Providing the Standardization Department with a hard copy/soft version of the
accepted/ approved Operations Manual;
Distributing its related Operations Manual and/or its amendments to all concerned
operations personnel, to ensure appropriate availability at points of use;
As required, identification, update, distribution and retention of documents of external
origin;
Disposal of obsolete documents.

2 Nominated Postholders

Issue: 5-Revision: 1 - 1 OCT 21
CEO (Accountable Executive);
G.M. Flight Operations;
G.M. Safety, Quality and Standardization;
Chief Pilots;
Maintenance Director;
