ORGANIZATION AND RESPONSIBILITIES

4 General Manager Integrated Operation Control Center (IOCC)

* Issue: 6-Revision: 2 - 15 OCT 24
This post falls within the Flight Operations Sector;
He supervises the Flight Operations, and controls the Dispatch departments and its staff;
The occupant of the post is subject to the direct supervision of the V.P Flight Operations
Sector. The G.M. IOCC is responsible to V.P. Flight Operations Sector for:
Overall responsibility for the execution of the Quality, Safety and Security policies and
instructions within the integrated operation control center departments and related to
operational control management;
Overall responsibility for the execution of the operational control in accordance with
applicable regulations and standards of EGYPTAIR and the ECAA. Duties and Responsibilities of the Post

Ensuring the functionality of the Safety, Quality, and Security Management Systems within the
Integrated Operations Control Center (IOCC) departments;
Ensuring high levels of performance and efficiency within the Integrated Operations Control
Center (IOCC) department;
Supervises and controls all flights through operational control functions and any other
associated activities;
The occupant of the post supervises all necessary measures to ensure the regularity of flights,
in coordination with all involved departments;
Supervises the routing of flights in accordance with the Operations Manual;
Lays down systems that provide pilots with the necessary information and documents related
to Route Manuals, in order to achieve the standards of safety, security, and operational
efficiency;
In coordination with the G.M.

Flight Operations and any other relevant entities, supervises the
implementation of necessary measures and courses of action in the event of any incident
and/or accident involving EGYPTAIR aircraft, as required;
Assures the execution of EGYPTAIR flight schedules in compliance with ECAR, Operations
Specifications, company policy, and the legislation of the other applicable authorities;
Establishes systems to ensure compliance with established instructions, rules, internal policies,
procedures, and information regarding flight operations, and makes any necessary
amendments to these systems as required;
May change the routing of flights when necessitated by operations (due to bad weather
conditions or otherwise) in order to secure flight safety and security, with close coordination
in this respect with the central control;
ORGANIZATION AND RESPONSIBILITIES

Additionally, inspect workplaces regularly to identify potential safety hazards and implement
effective corrective actions to permanently eliminate those hazards;
Carries out any other tasks assigned to him by the Chairman;
Liaises with external entities, such as service providers associated with the operational control
of flights, to ensure that all requirements affecting the safety and security of flight operations
are fulfilled by these service providers. Additionally, monitors contracted service personnel for
compliance;
Establishes an effective communication system with continuous monitoring, capable of
promptly distributing safety-critical and operational information —relevant to the safe
conduct of each flight— such as administrative circulars and operational bulletins, throughout
the operational control management system, ensuring their accuracy, timely updates, and
relevance to the working environment;
Strict compliance with the instructions and duties as indicated in the Operations Manual;
Supervises the execution of flight operation control responsibilities, authorities, and other
associated activities for the subordinates within the flight dispatcher departments to ensure
that all responsibilities, authorities, and other associated activities are implemented correctly
to meet the rules of operation control, quality, safety, and security policies and instructions;
Ensures the accuracy and validity of the Flight Dispatch Manual, including its issues,
amendments, and revisions, to guarantee that all instructions and information are up-to-date
with current regulations, company policies, and other applicable authorities in the working
environment;
Participates in all committees for the technical evaluation of new flight dispatchers and
personal interviews as a member of the committee, or nominates a deputy to attend on his
behalf;
Participates in the EGYPTAIR management review board;
ORGANIZATION AND RESPONSIBILITIES

