The Cabin Crew will direct passengers to identify and check their hand baggage and
wardrobe;
If suspicious article is found, the Commander will make a PA announcement asking for an
( EOD ) (Bomb Disposal Expert), and ATC shall be informed of the situation as soon as possible;
If a diversion is needed, the Commander shall inform passengers that the diversion ordered
by the company, without mentioning the Bomb Threat;
It is not necessary to declare emergency. Refer to Chapter 11.3.4 Reporting Hazardous Flight Conditions to ATC. NOTE OM Part B Bomb onboard procedures must be applied, if applicable. NOTE For Bomb/suspicious article handling procedures, refer to the OM Part F. NOTE For Least Risk Bomb Location, refer to OM Part B and the Suspicious Article Search
checklist. The action to be taken after landing will depend on whether or not a suspect item has been found
